The paper deals with the application of deep learning techniques, specifically the CycleGAN framework, on medical images for the purpose of reconstructing facial features from anonymized data. This falls under the domain of computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper discusses the need for anonymization in medical data sharing, which relates to the field of computer security (cs.CR). The use of deep learning also suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG).
